Commentary Text: Umesh Yadav to W Saha, out Caught by Venkatesh Iyer!! Umesh has the last laugh! Saha wanted to repeat the paddle scoop again, but the line was much wider this time and forced him to go on the off-side. Not in any position though for the shot and pops an absolute dolly to backward point. Not a bad wicket at this stage for Gujarat, because Saha wasn't able to get the run rate going. He's more than done his part though, shepherding the innings after the early loss of Gill. Platform is now set for some of the other powerhitters to come to the crease. Commentary Text: Southee to Shubman Gill, out Caught by Billings!! As soft a dismissal as you'd ever see! Gill is almost in disbelief at what he's just done and stands there for a moment before walking off. Southee can't believe his luck, it's nothing more than a harmless delivery going down the leg-side, would certainly have been wided but Gill tries to glance it fine, and gets the faintest of edges on this. Billings pouches it sharply with a tumble across and the KKR camp are chuffed to bits. It's a big wicket, because Gujarat's batting isn't that deep and Gill has been in top form this season. Commentary Text: Ferguson to Nitish Rana, out Caught by W Saha!! Appeal for caught behind. not given. Saha appealed as well. So they discuss and review. Ball very close to the bat says third ump. Anxious faces from the KKR fans. Was there a faint tickle? Oh yes, big spike and KKR are three down. Abhinav Mukund on air was the only one to say "I heard a nick from the stump mic" instantly. But this is another ugly dismissal the KKR coach won't be happy about. You just cannot show that you fear facing the short ball to a pacy bowler at this level. Rana was expecting a short ball, so never covered the line. Exposed the stumps with feet cemented and just pokes at the ball as Ferguson bowls a normal length delivery. Absolutely no control whatsoever. Saha and the bowler convinced Hardik for the review and got the verdict overturned. Nitish Rana c W Saha b Ferguson 2(7)
